Description: Part of a conical jar-seal: of red-brown clay, bearing two impressed inscriptions. Surface of clay rather friable.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XVIII, 1; H. R. Hall, 'Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs etc. in the British Museum: Volume 1 : Royal scarabs' (London, 1913), 287, no.2754; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pls.16, abb.32B; 33, abb. 101; see also vols. I, 82 and II, 686, n.44; 743, n. 402; 1097.
